import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='engineers', y='population', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the percentage of engineers and the population in each state?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='engineers', data=data)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest percentage of engineers?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    max_engineers_state = data.loc[data['engineers'].idxmax()]['state']
    max_engineers_value = data['engineers'].max()
    plt.axhline(max_engineers_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"{max_engineers_state}: {max_engineers_value:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    high_hurricane_states = data[data['hurricanes'] > data['hurricanes'].quantile(0.75)]
    avg_engineers = high_hurricane_states['engineers'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='engineers', data=high_hurricane_states)
    plt.axhline(avg_engineers, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_engineers:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average percentage of engineers in states with high hurricane activity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
